                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 13: Pyramid Saimira said some financial institutions had sold off pledged shares of two promoters against short-term loans taken by the company to overcome a liquidity crunch. Earlier, the company had said that one of its promoters, P. S. Saminathan had sold 17.07 lakh shares representing a 6.04 per cent stake between December 20 and December 31, 2008.                             
	 Ahmedabad, Jan. 13: Arun Kumar Jagatramka, vice-chairman and managing director of Gujarat NRE Coke Limited today announced at the Vibrant Gujarat Global Investors Summit that the group has plans to invest around Rs 3,000 crore in Gujarat over the next five years.                                                                                                                           
